I look forward to the greetings when I lumber in around 1030 for my americano, steamed heavy cream. Very nicely laid out Starbucks, that always seems busier than possible. Whenever I come in to this Starbucks to get a sweet treat, the line is almost out the door and the tables are almost always filled. Service works as fast as they can go, given the total onslaught of people ordering, so don't be surprised if your drink takes a bit of time to be made. Getting a seat in here is a struggle as many people seem to treat it as a lounge, sitting around with a token coffee cup packing textbooks and computers for working and studying. If you're going to order from here, do it with the intention of taking it to go, and I'd recommend using the order ahead  The baristas here do get major credit for correcting my order when it wasn't what I wanted. I accidentally ordered a cream frappuchino, and after it was made, they gladly remade it with a coffee base instead

I don't go to any Starbucks location often, but I decided to go to this one since it's close to my house. It turned out to be a very nice experience. I know the store can get crowded, but I went on a weeknight evening & the line was very short. The barista was awesome...we had a great conversation & she was quite helpful (as well as cute). She was speaking with a girl who she was training when I got to the register, but stopped right away to acknowledge me & assist. I was a bit overwhelmed by the menu, but finally figured out what to get, which was more than I'd anticipated. The variety, in my opinion, has always been a strength of this company, and this location has tons of different items to order. Yes, the prices are higher than other coffee places nearby, but I like the uniqueness of many of their products. There's metered street parking available right in front for those that want it. This probably isn't the typical Starbucks location, but I'm glad the business is here. I have nothing but good things to say.
